  <name>AutoSubSync</name>
  <summary>Automatic subtitle synchronization tool</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      AutoSubSync is a user-friendly tool that automatically synchronizes your subtitles with your videos using powerful tools such as ffsubsync, autosubsync, and alass.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Automatic synchronization using multiple sync engines (ffsubsync, autosubsync, alass)</li>
      <li>Manual subtitle adjustment with millisecond precision</li>
      <li>Batch processing for multiple video-subtitle pairs</li>
      <li>Support for multiple subtitle formats (SRT, VTT, SSA, ASS, and more)</li>
      <li>Subtitle extraction from embedded video files</li>
      <li>Sync tracking to avoid re-processing videos</li>
      <li>Library manager for organizing media files</li>
      <li>Auto-pairing with season/episode detection</li>
      <li>Support for 23+ interface languages</li>
      <li>Cross-platform compatibility (Windows, macOS, Linux)</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
